All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Administrator
Represents an Administrator in the hospital system.
AdministratorContainer
Container class for managing Administrator records.
AdministratorMenu
Menu class to manage various administrative operations in the Hospital Management System.
Appointment
Represents an appointment between a patient and a doctor in the hospital system.
AppointmentContainer
Container class for managing appointment records.
AppointmentOutcomeRecord
Represents an appointment outcome record, which contains information about the outcome of an appointment, including consultation notes, service type, and prescriptions.
AppointmentOutcomeRecordContainer
Container class for managing appointment outcome records.
Container
Marker interface to serve as a common type for all container classes.
Doctor
Represents a doctor in the hospital system.
DoctorContainer
Container class for managing Doctor records.
DoctorMenu
The DoctorMenu class provides a menu interface for a doctor to interact with the system.
Main
The main class for running the Hospital Management System (HMS).
MedicalRecord
Represents the medical record of a patient, which contains information such as diagnoses and treatment plans.
Medicine
Represents a Medicine record, which contains information about the medicine's name, current stock, and alert threshold for replenishment.
MedicineContainer
Container class for managing medicine records.
Menu
Abstract class representing a menu in the system.
Patient
Represents a patient in the hospital system.
PatientContainer
Container class for managing Patient records.
PatientMenu
PatientMenu represents a menu specifically for patients, allowing them to manage their medical records, appointments, and personal contact information.
Pharmacist
Represents a pharmacist in the hospital system.
PharmacistContainer
Container class for managing Pharmacist records.
PharmacistMenu
The PharmacistMenu class represents the menu specifically for pharmacists.
Prescription
Represents a prescription for a specific medicine with details including medicine name, prescribed amount, and the status of the prescription.
Record
Represents an abstract record with a unique identifier.
RecordContainer
Container class for managing general records.
ReplenishmentRequest
Represents a replenishment request for a specific medicine.
ReplenishmentRequestContainer
Container class for managing replenishment requests.
Staff
Represents a staff member in the hospital system.
StaffContainer
Container class for managing Staff records, including Doctors, Pharmacists, and Administrators.
StartMenu
The StartMenu class represents the main entry point for users accessing the hospital management system.
User
Represents an abstract user in the hospital management system.
UserContainer
Container class for managing User records.
